ct-nat-geo-tv-america-the-wild","created_at":1499866497359,"updated_at":1516587125049,"summary":"Part of Microsoft's \"playful learning\" initiative, Kinect Nat Geo TV uses augmented reality and motion-controlled activities to let young gamers learn and play with wildlife as they take part in interactive episodes of Nat Geo Wild TV. Players can explore habitats, take on the role of animals like bears and owls, speak up or gesture to learn more when they see something interesting, meet exotic animals, and solve mysterious puzzles. There are eight 30-minutes episodes in all, and gamers can also access archived clips of the TV series or view classic National Geographic photos.","collection":2986,"popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[34919,36608,16468,59516,23175,28029,37067,55289,10039,25646],"tags":[1,268435463,536872622,536874139,536875049,536875294,536876101,536877563,536879582],"category":0,"keywords":[1710,3227,4137,4382,5189,6651,8670],"themes":[1],"genres":[7],"first_release_date":1350518400000,"platforms":[12],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":12,"date":1350518400000,"region":8,"human":"2012-Oct-18","y":2012,"m":10}],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/iadgfcjmgpelxskm3m8a.jpg","cloudinary_id":"iadgfcjmgpelxskm3m8a","width":1541,"height":2169}},{"id":47393,"name":"Carnival Games: Monkey See, Monkey Do","slug":"carnival-games-monkey-see-monkey-do","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/carnival-games-monkey-see-monkey-do","created_at":1499866500465,"updated_at":1515557536702,"summary":"Get ready for a dip in the Shark Tank, a raucous ride on Coin Coaster Mountain or a Cotton-Eyed Joe dance-off with the Monkey Barker. Carnival Games:Monkey See, Monkey Do was made specifically to take full advantage of the innovative Kinect technology, offering easy access to all the thrills and fun of Carnival Games. Corner to Whirligig Way -- set the stage for gamers to swing away in the batting cage, avoid twisting tornadoes in the Hot Air Balloon Race, take a galactic journey to the red planet in Rocket to Mars and much more. \n \nClassic games like Alley Ball, Milk Bottle Throw and Wheel of Chance add to the family fun. All manner of interactive prizes and surprises abound, including pet dragons, robot cowboys, flying bears and ninja masks. \n \n \n \nIn addition, Kinect for Xbox 360's voice recognition technology allows The Amazing Wodin, a wily wizard with a weakness for wit, to advise players of their future. Also making his debut appearance in a Carnival Games title, is the Monkey Barker. Smartly dressed and renowned for his dancing skills, he promises to bring a fair share of monkey mischief to the midway.","collection":2494,"rating":70.0,"popularity":1.333333333333333,"total_rating":70.0,"total_rating_count":0,"rating_count":0,"games":[36608,2940,40524,34919,71581,29660,1070,23175,76438,16468],"tags":[1],"category":0,"keywords":[95,684,946],"themes":[1],"genres":[13,33],"first_release_date":1304553600000,"platforms":[12],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":12,"date":1304553600000,"region":8,"human":"2011-May-05","y":2011,"m":5}],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/rtsh6yfddgwnfj6b8vlq.jpg","cloudinary_id":"rtsh6yfddgwnfj6b8vlq","width":600,"height":600},"websites":[{"category":2,"url":"http://vgw.wikia.com/wiki/Carnival_Games:_Monkey_See,_Monkey_Do"}]},{"id":47394,"name":"Duplicate - Body and Brain Connection","slug":"duplicate-body-and-brain-connection","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/duplicate-body-and-brain-connection","created_at":1499866502906,"updated_at":1509488891143,"popularity":1.333333333333333,"category":0,"keywords":[1094]},{"id":47395,"name":"Forza Motorsport 4: Essentials Edition","slug":"forza-motorsport-4-essentials-edition","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/forza-motorsport-4-essentials-edition","created_at":1499866505287,"updated_at":1517394245328,"summary":"Forza Motorsport 4 is a racing video game developed by Turn 10 Studios and published by Microsoft Studios for the Xbox 360. It is the fourth installment in the Forza Motorsport series. It is the first title in the series to support the Kinect sensor alongside the traditional controller-based gameplay. \n \nNew to the series is the Autovista mode, a mode in which players can view precise details such as engine parts and interior gauges on a select number of cars. It features a partnership with BBC's Top Gear as well as its American counterpart. Jeremy Clarkson, presenter for Top Gear, provides commentary in the game's Autovista mode. Other partnerships include a two-year agreement with the American Le Mans Series (ALMS). Over 500 cars and 26 tracks are included. \n \nThe game received universal acclaim from critics. Aggregate websites GameRankings and Metacritic report scores of 90.50% and 91 out of 100, respectively. Metacritic also reports eight perfect scores from various media outlets. Critics praised the enhanced vehicle physics, updated visuals, and strong sound design. Several reviewers also gave high marks for the Forza 4 '​s Autovista mode. Some critics expressed frustration with Kinect features, and others also felt that the game was not enough of an innovation from its predecessor, Forza Motorsport 3. These critics did, however, concede that the game was a vast improvement over Forza 3.","popularity":1.333333333333333,"version_parent":3068,"version_title":"Essentials Edition","games":[23314,18699,76259,103018,101535,101205,101142,101087,100902,100844],"tags":[268435466],"category":0,"genres":[10],"first_release_date":1352419200000,"platforms":[12],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":12,"date":1352419200000,"region":8,"human":"2012-Nov-09","y":2012,"m":11}],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/u2zufgrvjm0rpppwppan.jpg","cloudinary_id":"u2zufgrvjm0rpppwppan","width":1006,"height":1169}},{"id":47396,"name":"11 Eyes: CrossOver","slug":"11-eyes-crossover","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/11-eyes-crossover","created_at":14998