 games by obtaining permission from the Professional Baseball Organization of Japan to use the official names of the 12 Japanese baseball teams and their players. This was a groundbreaking feature at the time. It was also the first game to depict an existing stadium with it's actual name, the Tokyo Dome, which had just opened shortly before the game's release. Outfielder and first baseman Warren Cromartie, formerly with the Montreal Expos, and playing for the Yomiuri Giants at the time, was chosen to help promote the game. \n \nTo further distinguish the game, the developers chose to use a more realistic approach when depicting the players on the field, as opposed to the more cartoonish look utilized by Pro Yakyuu Family Stadium and many other baseball games. Additionally, the view remains fairly close to the ball after the batter hits the ball, as opposed to zooming out to a bird's eye view of the field. Despite these changes, and efforts to promote the game, it was considered very difficult to play, as it employed rather complex controls for batting, pitching, and fielding that were not easy for many players to perform.","popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[69398,67390,66208,66197,65284,64377,64044,62299,62275,62254],"tags":[268435470,536870932],"category":0,"keywords":[20],"genres":[14],"first_release_date":588902400000,"platforms":[18],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":18,"date":588902400000,"region":8,"human":"1988-Aug-30","y":1988,"m":8}],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/ahfjuff8s6xnvchb2gfc.jpg","cloudinary_id":"ahfjuff8s6xnvchb2gfc","width":424,"height":600}},{"id":48396,"name":"Sherlock Holmes: Hakushaku Reijou Yuukai Jiken","slug":"sherlock-holmes-hakushaku-reijou-yuukai-jiken","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/sherlock-holmes-hakushaku-reijou-yuukai-jiken","created_at":1499965225042,"updated_at":1516739778383,"summary":"Sherlock Holmes: Hakushaku Reijou Yuukai Jiken (loosely translated as Sherlock Homes: Kidnapping of the Young Countess) is an adventure game developed for the Famicom by Towachiki, and released in 1986. The game puts the player in the role of Sherlock Holmes, who must travel throughout England (by train) while trying to solve the mystery of a kidnapping. In this unusual portrayal of Holmes, his only means of interrogating anyone to obtain information is by attacking them with jump kicks until they run out of stamina and reveal clues. The game alternates between a zoomed out view of England streets, where every bystander can damage Holmes simply by running in to him, to a zoomed in side scrolling view of buildings or sewers or parks. Besides interrogating people for information, or simply beating them up for train fare, Holmes must search seemingly random cracks or trees in order to find important clues, or inventory items.","collection":3385,"popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[37088,47823,19289,16468,26848,1221,59516,27314,13189,23175],"tags":[1,17,22,268435487,536871939,536872581,536875054,536875058,536875067,536876208,536877451],"category":0,"keywords":[1027,1669,4142,4146,4155,5296,6539],"themes":[1,17,22],"genres":[31],"first_release_date":534643200000,"platforms":[18],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":18,"date":534643200000,"region":5,"human":"1986-Dec-11","y":1986,"m":12},{"category":0,"platform":18,"date":537321600000,"region":8,"human":"1987-Jan-11","y":1987,"m":1}],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/e24xokztvfmkcgqqxdlm.jpg","cloudinary_id":"e24xokztvfmkcgqqxdlm","width":265,"height":384}},{"id":48397,"name":"Shadow Brain","slug":"shadow-brain","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/shadow-brain","created_at":1499965227463,"updated_at":1500370463475,"summary":"Shadow Brain is a Role-Playing game, developed by Scitron \u0026 Art and published by Pony Canyon, which was released in Japan in 1991.","popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[49414,25636,21842,28080,36608,18862,75102,23913,47472,44922],"tags":[268435468],"category"