ing video game for the Japanese version of the NES, the Famicom. It was developed by NHK and published by Victor Interactive Software (now Marvelous Entertainment) in 1991. The game was only released in Japan. \n \nThe player controls the main protagonist, an exiled prince of LittleLand that has been recently informed of his royal heritage. To reclaim the throne, the prince must collect seven shards of the Rainbow Mirror and defeat the usurper, Zrool. The shards are scattered throughout South Asia and the prince must trade goods to make his way to each region. Once the mirror is collected, the prince shines it at Zrool and exposes the imposter. The prince then takes his throne as the new king.","popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[72412,26766,59516,55289,25300,18398,13189,36926,36534,36792],"tags":[268435468,268435487,536871938,536871939],"category":0,"keywords":[1026,1027],"genres":[12,31],"first_release_date":669600000000,"platforms":[18],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":18,"date":669600000000,"region":8,"human":"1991-Mar-22","y":1991,"m":3}],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/ywlcdeewdxrijfzr678b.jpg","cloudinary_id":"ywlcdeewdxrijfzr678b","width":299,"height":202}},{"id":48410,"name":"Nekketsu Kakutou Densetsu","slug":"nekketsu-kakutou-densetsu","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/nekketsu-kakutou-densetsu","created_at":1499965326357,"updated_at":1518075309624,"summary":"One day at school, Kunio was minding his own business when suddenly, he found a note on his locker. The note says their is a fighting tournament hosted by the \"Double Tiger\" twins. Seeing it as a challenge he could not refuse, Kunio runs off to participate. When Riki sees Kunio running and read his note, he decides to enter as well. Many other fighters will join in to see who is the strongest.","popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[41828,10039,22418,65832,19333,1235,55752,68391,7100,36911],"tags":[1,268435460,536870973,536871019,536871801,536871889,53687197